OL,5, Rail unions have reacted with fury to a
OL,6, government threat to make strike action
OL,7, illegal unless a minimum number of     
OL,8, train staff work during a walkout.     
OL,10,FTransport Secretary Grant Shapps said a
OL,11,Flaw would protect freight shipments of 
OL,12,Fgoods such as food and fuel.           
OL,14,FBut unions vowed "fierce resistance" to
OL,15,Fany curb on the right to strike,       
OL,16,Fcalling the move "authoritarian" and   
OL,17,F"desperate nonsense".                  
OL,19,FSome 40,000 rail workers are being     
OL,20,Fballoted over taking industrial action.
